parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake calipers can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side when braking, leading to accidents or loss of control.

vibration or pulsation when braking

symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents or loss of control, especially when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially fatalities.

failure to stop or slow down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of cruise control can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the speed control system can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door and Trunk Release Mechanism Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door and trunk release mechanism can cause the doors and trunk to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door or trunk will not open
the key remote does not work
the door or trunk has no key latch on the outside
the passenger door or trunk cannot be opened from the outside
the door or trunk cannot be opened from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding door cable can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to open or close the door, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power sliding door cable snapped
the door cannot be opened or closed
the door is stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loose or falling interior panels can cause distractions while driving, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
